Biography

Dr. Saty Raghavachary is a Senior Lecturer at the CS Dept, where he teaches courses
on computer graphics (CG), databases and introductory programming. From 2004-
2014 he was a part-time lecturer in CS, during which time he taught graphics and
animation courses.

Before joining USC full-time, Saty was a Designated Support Specialist at Autodesk
Inc., makers of Maya, Softimage, 30S Max, AutoCAD and several other industry-
leading software tools. Prior to joining Autodesk, Saty spent 16 wonderful years at
DreamWorks Feature Animation (with screen credits in 20 mayies, including Puss in
Boots, How to Train Your Dragon, Kung Fu Panda and Shreka), where he developed
CG software tools in the R&D department, and trained incoming artists on the tools
and pipeline. Before that, he was Software Manager at MetroLight Studios, one of
the pioneering visual effects studios in Hollywood during the late 80s and early 90s.

Saty has published two popular books on RenderMan, the CG industry's leading
rendering software. He is working on a third book, on Maya Python. Saty also gives
talks to schools and colleges in the LA area (eg. Cal Lutheran, LMU, GCC) on
animation production and CG.

Saty obtained three MS degrees and PhD at The Ohio State University, and also did
postdoctoral research there. He is a member of ACM, IEEE (Computer Society), ASEE
and American Mensa.
